rules_version = '2';

// Firestore rules for the family games (project wordvoyage-e5a5c).
//
// Every game vendors gamekit and syncs to its own top-level collection:
//   wordvoyage · chickencross · blockparty · biblequest · brickbreaker · deepjungle
// with docs profile_<id>, progress_<id> and deleted_<id>.
//
// These rules are NOT applied by deploying this repo -- paste them into the
// Firebase console (Firestore Database -> Rules) or run `firebase deploy
// --only firestore:rules`. The file lives here so the intended state is in
// version control rather than only in a web console.
//
// What changed and why: the rules previously allowed unauthenticated read and
// write. The Firebase config is public in every page load, so anyone who
// viewed source could read or wipe the family's saved progress. gk-storage.js
// now signs in anonymously on boot, so requiring an auth token costs the
// players nothing and stops drive-by scripts.
//
// ROLLOUT ORDER MATTERS -- applying these before every game ships the
// anonymous-auth build will silently drop all six games back to
// localStorage-only:
//   1. Enable Authentication -> Sign-in method -> Anonymous in the console.
//   2. Ship gamekit >= 1.3.0 to every game (re-vendor + deploy).
//   3. Only then apply these rules.
//
// Anonymous uids are per-device, so they cannot be used to scope a document to
// an owner: the whole point is that the family shares one roster across
// devices and phones. Auth here is a gate, not an ownership model.
//
// Collections are enumerated rather than matched with a wildcard. The existing
// rules already deny unknown collections -- a probe against a made-up name
// fails with "Missing or insufficient permissions" while the game collections
// allow unauthenticated read AND write -- so a wildcard would widen access
// while appearing to tighten it.
//
// NOTE: the API key has HTTP-referrer restrictions. Anonymous sign-in is
// blocked from origins that aren't on the allowlist (localhost included, which
// is why this can't be verified from a dev server). Before applying these
// rules, confirm on the live https://rvenning.github.io origin that sign-in
// actually succeeds -- otherwise every game silently drops to local-only.
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /{collection}/{document} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null
        && collection in ["wordvoyage", "chickencross", "blockparty",
                          "biblequest", "brickbreaker", "deepjungle"];
    }
  }
}
